<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 7:06AM EST  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Paulding, Cherokee,
Haralson, northern Carroll, southwestern Gilmer, Floyd, Gordon, Polk,
Pickens and Bartow Counties through 800 AM EST...
At 705 AM EST, a thunderstorm producing moderate to heavy rainfall
was near Taylorsville, or 13 miles west of Cartersville, moving
northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Rome, Carrollton, Canton, Cartersville, Calhoun, Dallas, Cedartown,
Jasper, Buchanan, Villa Rica, Bremen, Adairsville, Temple, Rockmart,
Euharlee, Hiram, Tallapoosa, Mount Zion, Emerson and Ball Ground.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
